LanguageAndText

Class TextNameConstants

  • java.lang.Object
    • LanguageAndText.TextNameConstants

  • public abstract class TextNameConstants
extends java.lang.Object
    This class contains solely constants for property names in the properties files "title" and "properties". In these properties files the value of the string is used for the property name. For example is in the title-properties file a property saved for "ADDITION" - Constant TITLE_ADDITION. So this file represents a standard for names used in the property files.

    Use this in combination with the ITextFacade as follows:
    ITextFacade myTextFacade = ITextFacade.getInstance(); //creating an ITextFacade object
    String titleForAddition = myTextFacade.getTitle(TextNameConstants.TITLE_ADDITION);
     As a result the string titleForAddition has now the value of the title which the property file contains for "ADDITION".

    If you create or edit a property file please confirm that the constant is entered in this class and also corresponds to the name given in the property file.

    For the property file "button" the names are standardized in ViewActions.
    All the names and more for the "dialog"-property file are specified in an one class DialogConstants, in which next to the name strings also the standard buttons for each dialog are given. The titles of dialogs are still defined in the title property file. Due to this the TITLE_... constant in this file and DIALOG_... in DialogConstants must be excluding each other.

    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    9045534
    See Also:
    ITextFacade, ViewActions, DialogConstants
